INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(74, 'Masterplan for Seekers of the Ashen Crown', 'masterplan-for-seekers-of-the-ashen-crown', '', '<p>This is incomplete as I am starting the adventure at encounter 7</p>\n<p><a href="dnd/adventures/seekers+of+the+ashen+crown/Seekers%20of%20the%20Ashen%20Crown.htm">http://caitlain.com/dnd/adventures/seekers+of+the+ashen+crown/Seekers%20of%20the%20Ashen%20Crown.htm</a></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Dnd4e Combat Manager version:</p>\n<p><a href="http://caitlain.com/dnd/adventures/seekers+of+the+ashen+crown/AshenCrown.7z">http://caitlain.com/dnd/adventures/seekers+of+the+ashen+crown/AshenCrown.7z</a></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>', '', 1, 5, 0, 35, '2011-03-31 20:00:41', 62, 'matt@caitlain.com', '2011-03-31 20:10:01', 62, 62, '2016-08-20 00:34:06', '2011-03-31 19:59:39', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 2, 0, 4, '', '', 0, 9844, '');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(75, 'Eyes of the Lich Queen Conversion', 'eyes-of-the-lich-queen-conversion', '', '<p>Below are my <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Dungeons-Dragons-Fantasy-Roleplaying-Eberron/dp/078694319X/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&s=books&qid=1301614714&sr=8-1" title="Eyes of the Lich Queen">Eyes of the Lich Queen</a> conversions based on the methodology discussed <a href="index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=73:converting-35e-adventures-to-4e&catid=35:dad-4e&Itemid=56" title="here">here</a>:</p>\r\n<p><a href="dnd/mystuff/Lich%20Queen/Eyes%20of%20the%20Lich%20Queen.htm" title="Masterplan style">Masterplan style</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="dnd/mystuff/Lich%20Queen/LichQueen.7z" title="DnD 4e Combat Manager style">DnD4e Combat Manager style</a></p>\r\n<p>The major difference between how I did the conversions for <a href="http://masterplan.habitualindolence.net/" title="Masterplan">Masterplan</a> and how I did them for the <a href="http://wiki.rpg.net/index.php/DnD4eCM">DnD4e Combat Manager</a> is how I converted the NPCs in the adventure. For Masterplan, I calculated how much XP they should be worth, found a monster already created in 4e that was close to the description of the character,  and then adjusted that monster''s level to get the right XP. For DnD4eCM, I actually created characters in the online <a href="http://wizards.com/dnd/Tool.aspx?x=dnd/4new/tool/characterbuilder" title="Wizards.com Online Character Builder">Character Builder</a> and exported their .dnd4e character builder files to my hard drive and then imported these character builder files into DnD4eCM. Once they are in the tool, you change their type from "Hero" to one of the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/DnD4eCM/165885120116832" title="facebook discussion of this topic">monster types</a> and you can then use them as combatants in the encounters.</p>\r\n<p><a href="dnd/mystuff/Lich%20Queen/LichQueen.7z"></a></p>', '', 1, 5, 0, 35, '2011-03-31 23:28:13', 62, 'matt@caitlain.com', '2018-04-17 00:14:56', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-03-31 23:23:25', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 13, 0, 3, '', '', 0, 10688, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(76, 'D&D Counters Ready for Printing', 'dad-counters-ready-for-printing', '', '<p>Here is a powerpoint deck of counters that are ready for printing. The counters came from<a href="http://dndcounters.tripod.com/">http://dndcounters.tripod.com/</a> and are mostly from the original art found in the 3.5e Monster Manuals. I resized the graphics so that when they are printed on 8.5 in x 11 in paper they will be the standard size for 1 in x 1 in grids. I usually print these out on photopaper,  laminate the sheet and then cut the counters out. Before laminating,   it probably makes sense to label the identical monsters with a "1",   "2", "3", etc. Gel ink works best for writing on the photopaper before lamination.</p>\n<p>If anyone has any free counters for 4e edition, let us know.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.caitlain.com/dnd/tools/Counters.pptx" title="Counter Deck">Counter Deck</a></p>\n<p></p>', '', 1, 5, 0, 35, '2011-04-02 19:54:31', 62, 'matt@caitlain.com', '2016-08-20 00:33:22', 62, 62, '2016-08-20 00:33:24', '2011-04-02 19:47:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 5, 0, 2, '', '', 0, 14259, '');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(77, 'How to batch unzip a bunch of files', 'how-to-batch-unzip-a-bunch-of-files', '', '<p>there was a locked archive thread on the ubuntu forums that did not have what I consider the best solution for this. Here is how I do it:</p>\n<pre>for i in *.zip\ndo\nmkdir "${i%.zip}"\nunzip "$i" -d "${i%.zip}"\ndone</pre>\n<p>The solution I use is to create a subdirectory for each of the archives before unzipping it. The names of the zip files are stored in the variable $i. Since there may be spaces in the filenames,   you will need to refer to $i as "$i" within the script. In order to create a directory that does not include the ".zip" in its name,   you need to replace it with "nothing". That is done by:</p>\n<pre style="color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; margin: 8px;">mkdir "${i%.zip}"</pre>\n<div>If we had used the command</div>\n<div>\n<pre style="color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; margin: 8px;">mkdir "$i"</pre>\n<p>instead, then for a file named "abc def.zip" we would get a directory named "abc def.zip". However, if we use the "${i%.zip}" instead of "$i" we just get a directory named "abc def". As a note, if you wanted to strip off the .zip and replace it with something else, say "+dir" you could do the following:</p>\n<pre style="color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; margin: 8px;">mkdir "${i%.zip}+dir"</pre>\n</div>', '', 1, 1, 0, 37, '2011-04-03 15:31:17', 62, '', '2016-08-20 00:42:27', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-04-03 15:19:41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 5, 0, 6, '', '', 0, 10238, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(78, 'Masterplan for Pyramid of Shadows', 'masterplan-for-pyramid-of-shadows', '', '<p>Masterplan for <a href="dnd/adventures/pyramid+of+shadows/Pyramid%20of%20Shadows.htm" target="_blank" title="Pyramid of Shadows">Pyramid of Shadows</a></p>\n<p>Note: maps and treasure parcels are not complete yet.</p>\n<p>Tokens for the adventure are available <a href="dnd/adventures/pyramid+of+shadows/Pyramid%20Of%20Shadows-Token_Set.pdf" target="_blank" title="Token Set">here</a></p>', '', 1, 0, 0, 0, '2011-04-15 22:19:02', 62, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-04-15 22:15:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 1, 0, 11, '', '', 0, 2499, '');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(79, 'Gluten-free Mushroom & Sausage tacos', 'gluten-free-mushroom-a-sausage-tacos', '', '<p><strong style="font-family: ''lucida grande'',   tahoma,   verdana,   arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; ">Ingredients</strong></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">[Tacos]</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">6 Medium size porabellas<br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">1/2 lb sliced shitakes</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">6 Sausages (Bratwurst, Chicken Sausage, etc)</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">1/4 of a large Vidaia Onion</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">White Corn Tortillas</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">4 oz of<strong style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; ">Smoked</strong> Mozzarella cheese</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">[Rice side dish]</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">2 cups Basmati rice</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">Fresh Cilantro</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><strong style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; ">Taco directions:</strong></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">Heat the grill (charcoal only...if you are going to cook with gas, quit reading and go buy a charcoal grill) to about 300 F.  Place the sausages and portabellas to the side of the coals. Place a saute pan directly above the coals. Add about 1/4 cup of premium olive oil, the slices of onion and the shitakes in the saute pan.</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">As things are complete their cooking process, take them off of the coals and sit to the side to cool and rest. Most likely the onions and shitakes will complete first, then the sausages (especially if you get ones that are pre-cooked).</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">Let the meat and mushrooms cool enough to handle, and then dice them up. Warm the tortillas then place in a basket and cover with a towel (do this on the grill if possible, otherwise you could do it in a microwave). Place the saute pan back onto the grill and add the diced mushrooms and sausage to reheat as needed. Once everything is done, place the saute pan on a heat proof pad on your table and let people spoon out the warm mixture onto their tortillas. The mozzarella should be sliced thinly or crumbled so that it can be placed onto the tacos. I usually put the cheeze on first and then the meat/fungi/vegetable mixture second so that it will melt the cheese. You''ll love how the smoked moz tastes with the portabellas.</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><strong>Side dish:</strong></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><strong> </strong>Cook the rice according to the directions (will take about 30 minutes for basmti rice and you will need about 2x the liquid as the amount of rice). Once cooked, remove from heat. Cut up some of the cilantro and mix with the rice. Feel free to add a little of the mushroom to the rice if desired. I usually boil the water before I even light the coals for the grill. I usually cook the rice about 25 minutes and then let it sit for the rest of the grilling process above. If you cover the rice the entire time, the rice will still be plenty hot once the main dish is ready.</p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; "><br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; color: #000000; ">Note: If you don''t want to have tacos, you can easily change this into an appetizer. You will need<strong style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; ">large</strong> portabellas caps instead of mediums. You will also need only one sauasge per 2 portabella caps. I usually find that one person can eat a whole cap--but they can also easily be shared. Once the sasage and caps are done take them off the grill. Dice up the sausage but not the caps. You are going to put the diced sausage onto the caps and then place thinly sliced mozzarella over the top. Return to the grill and let the cheese melt and then you are done.<br style="font-family: ''lucida grande'', tahoma, verdana, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 16px; " /></p>\n<p></p>', '', 1, 6, 0, 36, '2011-05-30 14:29:46', 62, '', '2016-08-20 00:26:18', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-05-30 14:29:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 2, 0, 2, '', '', 0, 10777, '');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(80, 'Side dish needs a name', 'side-dish-needs-a-name', '', '<p><span style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em;">Came up with a pretty nice side dish last night. Not sure what to call it,   but here are the ingredients:</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 can chopped spinach</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 can of small artichokes</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 box of gluten-free cream of celery soup</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 bunch of asparagus</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">Drain as much of the liquids from the cans as possible. Heat the grill to a medium heat (250-300 degrees). Place asparagus on gratings to the side of the coals,   and place the spinach and artichokes in a large pan. Separate the artichokes as much as possible with a wooden spoon.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">After the spinach and artichokes warm nicely,   add the soup. Once the asparagus is done, remove everything from the grill.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">Plate the dish by laying down a few of the asparagus stems and cover with the spinach/asparagus/celery soup mix.</p>\n<p></p>', '', 1, 6, 0, 36, '2011-05-30 14:30:53', 62, '', '2016-08-20 00:26:25', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-05-30 14:30:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 3, 0, 1, '', '', 0, 9252, '');
