INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(84, 'Patience is a virtue', 'patience-is-a-virtue', '', '<p><span style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em;">Came up with a pretty nice side dish last night. Not sure what to call it,   but here are the ingredients:</span></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 can chopped spinach</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 can of small artichokes</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 box of gluten-free cream of celery soup</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">1 bunch of asparagus</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">Drain as much of the liquids from the cans as possible. Heat the grill to a medium heat (250-300 degrees). Place asparagus on gratings to the side of the coals,   and place the spinach and artichokes in a large pan. Separate the artichokes as much as possible with a wooden spoon.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">After the spinach and artichokes warm nicely,   add the soup. Once the asparagus is done, remove everything from the grill.</p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;"></p>\n<p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.5em; margin: 0px;">Plate the dish by laying down a few of the asparagus stems and cover with the spinach/asparagus/celery soup mix.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>A friend of mine was studying for the math portion of the GRE the other day,   and it made me think of this joke (which I first came across in <em>Gravity''s Rainbow</em>):</p>\n<p><img src="http://www.caitlain.com/images/2011-06-02_15-04-46_539.jpg" border="0" width="648" height="484" /></p>\n<p><img src="Ginny.jpg" border="0" /></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Ginny,   you were my best friend and I will miss you so much. We loved you will all our hearts and will always remember you.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><img src="Ginny.jpg" border="0" /></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>Ginny,   you were my best friend and I will miss you so much. We loved you very much and will always remember you.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>So,   I''m sitting in first class tonight and there is this delightful child up here with us. So often,   I dread having a young child in first class because they often cannot handle the 4+ hour trip between Los Angeles and Chicago without going completely bonkers--as a 42 year old who has done it about every week for 18 months, I know I hardly can. Anyway, while I was sitting here waiting to take off I thought, "I hope this child''s parent says something to the effect that patience is a virtue, giving them a chance to teach the child that having an attention span measured in hours instead of seconds is not such a bad thing.</p>\n<p>So, as I was hoping that this would occur, I started thinking about other things, like "how many virtues are there?". I know that there are "seven deadly sins"--mostly dealing with masturbation...like sloth (being too lazy to masturbate), gluttony (being to full to feel like masturbating), pride (being too full of yourself to masturbate), and wrath (being too angry to masturbate). However, I''ve never heard the correlative to the "sins". Are there official "virtues"? Am I just too much of a yokel to have never heard of them?</p>\n<p>Or, perhaps, we just spend too much time talking about the bad things...E.g, don''t do this, don''t do that. Wouldn''t we all be better off if we spent way less time talking about the "seven deadly sins" and way more time talking about the (more than seven--I hope) "virtues". I think that as a society we would be much better off trying to do better with our own lives--or at least the things that we have some hope of controlling--than spending so much of our time worrying about the things that we can''t directly control.</p>\n<p>...tbc</p>', '', -1, 1, 0, 3, '2012-08-31 02:44:48', 62, '', '2012-08-31 02:47:39', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2012-08-31 02:34:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 2, 0, 3, '', '', 0, 1392, 'robots=\nauthor=');
